4 HR____ CONGRATULATING OFFICER CYLE CUTCLIFF FOR HIS MANY
5 CONTRIBUTIONS TO THE HOOVER POLICE DEPARTMENT ON THE
6 OCCASION OF HIS RETIREMENT.
7
8 WHEREAS, Officer Cyle Cutcliff is retiring after 34
9 years of exemplary service to the Hoover Police Department,
10 having served with the utmost honor and distinction; and
11 WHEREAS, Cyle Cutcliff began pursuing a career in law
12 enforcement at an early age when he served as a Hoover
13 Police Explorer from 1988 to 1992, where he was exposed to
14 the profession and began a pathway to the career; from 1992
15 to 1995 he was a Jailer in the Hoover City Jail; and
16 WHEREAS, in 1995 Officer Cutcliff graduated from The
17 University of Alabama Law Enforcement Academy Basic Session
18 115 in Tuscaloosa; concluding his graduation, Officer
19 Cutcliff began his role as a Patrol Officer with the Hoover
20 Police Department, which he has excelled in for the
21 remainder of his career; he is set to retire in April 2026;
22 and
23 WHEREAS, in addition to his patrol duties, he was
24 able to make an impact on the force by contributing to the
25 experience and success of other officers; he served as a
26 Hoover Police Explorer Program Advisor and Field Training
27 Officer; he also served as a Crime Scene Investigator and
28 was assigned to the multiagency DEA Task Force; and
Page 1

was assigned to the multiagency DEA Task Force; and
HR272 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, over the course of his career, Officer
30 Cutcliff has been recognized on numerous occasions for his
31 service, including Law Enforcement Officer of the Year
32 presented by Shades Mountain Optimist Club in 2000, Hoover
33 Area Chamber of Commerce Police Officer of the Year in 2015,
34 and Hoover Police Department Meritorious Service Award in
35 2016; he has also been included as a finalist for Hoover
36 Area Chamber of Commerce Police Officer of the Year in 2011
37 and in 2018; and
38 WHEREAS, concluding his service to the Hoover Police
39 Department, Officer Cutcliff plans to enjoy time with his
40 wife, Kim Cutcliff; daughter and son, Emma and Colin; and
41 his best pal, two-year-old grandson, Luke Bradley; he will
42 be dividing his time between Birmingham and Smith Lake, and
43 he looks forward to golfing and traveling; and
44 WHEREAS, Officer Cutcliff has performed his duties
45 with the highest level of professionalism, integrity, and
46 excellence, and his positive impact on law enforcement in
47 Alabama will be felt for many years following his
48 retirement; now therefore,
49 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
50 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That Officer Cyle Cutcliff is
51 commended on the occasion of his retirement for outstanding
52 service to the Hoover Police Department, and we hereby
53 dedicate this resolution to him with heartfelt gratitude and
54 regard, along with sincere best wishes for continued
55 happiness.
